Contact Manager System - Project Documentation (Revised)
1. Abstract
The Contact Manager System is a console-based Python application designed to store and manage user contacts efficiently. 
It uses a dictionary data structure to perform operations like adding, viewing, searching, updating, and deleting contacts. 
The system is menu-driven and runs continuously until the user chooses to exit.
2. Introduction
In today’s digital world, managing contacts is essential. This project provides a simple solution for storing contact details 
using Python. It helps beginners understand how real-world applications handle data using basic programming concepts.
3. Objectives
• Develop a simple contact management system.
• Implement CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete).
• Understand Python dictionaries and loops.
• Build a user-friendly menu-driven program.
4. System Requirements
Hardware Requirements:
• Basic computer or laptop
Software Requirements:
• Python (version 3.x)
• Any IDE (VS Code, PyCharm, IDLE)
5. System Design
The system uses a while loop to repeatedly display a menu. Based on user input, different operations are performed. 
A dictionary stores contacts where the name is the key and phone number is the value.
6. Algorithm
1. Start the program
2. Initialize empty dictionary
3. Display menu options
4. Take user input
5. Perform selected operation
6. Repeat until user exits
7. Stop the program
7. Features
Add Contact – Adds new contact after checking duplicates.
View Contacts – Displays all contacts.
Search Contact – Finds contact by name.
Update Contact – Edits phone number.
Delete Contact – Removes a contact.
Exit – Terminates program.
8. Advantages
• Easy to implement
• Efficient data handling
• Beginner-friendly
• Fast operations using dictionary
9. Limitations
• No permanent storage
• No graphical interface
• Stores only basic details
10. Future Enhancements
• Add file/database storage
• GUI using Tkinter
• Additional fields like email
• Authentication system
11. Conclusion
The Contact Manager System is a simple yet effective project that demonstrates core Python concepts. 
It serves as a strong foundation for developing more advanced applications.
